Due to Apple's great relationship with Hollywood, you may have noticed that there are a lot of Macs popping up in movies and TV shows.  The Newton is no exception.  This is an attempt to document all of the sightings of Newtons in television, movies and other mainstream media.  Thanks to Rick Ludwig of [[NewtonTalk]] for writing [the initial list](http://www.newtontalk.net/archive/newtontalk.2004-02/0209.html] that this page is based on.  Also some of this information gleaned from various posts to [[NewtonTalk]) over the years.%%%
%%%

__Apple-sponsored media appearances__

* __[Newton TV Commercials](http://www.unna.org/view.php?/movies/commercials]__ : The original Newton TV spots.  In [[QuickTime]) format, some also in PKG format for viewing on the Newton itself.

* __[Knowledge Navigator](http://www.unna.org/view.php?/movies/Apple/KnowledgeNavigator)__ : While not strictly containing the Newton, this video was commissioned by John Sculley (Apple CEO 1985-1997) to show his vision of computing.  Part of the vision was a Personal Digital Assistant, and the rest is history...

